                        <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">

                                <p>
                                    As the diagram previously water heating is the second biggest energy that is used in the household.
                                    For every 60 litre of water heating, comparing the most common system that used by household there is about 39% people who is using electric,
                                    42% using gas, the rest are using solar and heat pump. Considering cost effective in long term,
                                    people who are using electric heating and are considering switching to new system can change to gas heating.


                                </p>
                                <br>
                                <p>
                                    From the sustainability Victoria, as
                                    <b>per 60 litre of water heating electric </b>cost you
                                    <b>$395-$555</b> while<b> gas heating</b> for same amount will be costing from <b>$160-$370</b>.
                                    From this data, it is easy to understand that every month electric heating user are paying double price for the energy usage on water heating.
                                    Not only that, electric produces the most green house gas emissions compare to the other system.
                                </p>
                                <p>
