                                    Out of 3 Australians only 1 people turned off their tap water when they are brushing their teeth.
                                    The water waste is an average of<b> 5.68L per minutes</b>. If a person brushes their teeth 2 or 3 times a day every time about 3 minutes that 15L water is wasted!
                                    The same with people who did not turn off their tap when they are washing their hands. Out of the research it shows half of the time the hands are not washing under the tap.
                                    Especially during the pandemic, people took longer time to wash their hands.
                                    So, turn off your tap water during brushing or washing your hands you will find that you save a lot of money and at the same time contribute good to environment just by
